---

## 🧭 System Context

The **Transformation Layer** serves as the **geospatial QA engine** for all hazard datasets flowing through KFM’s pipeline.  
It ensures all hazard data (from staging) adheres to **consistent CRS**, **CF-compliant attributes**, **temporal standardization**, and **checksum-verifiable reproducibility** before moving into validation or AI stages.

**Core Responsibilities**
- Reproject all geometries to **EPSG:4326** (standard CRS for interchange).  
- Normalize all metadata fields per **CF + FAIR conventions**.  
- Generate **COG** and **PMTiles** for optimized performance and offline compatibility.  
- Record all reprojection, resampling, and CF fixes in traceable logs.  
- Register transformation lineage and hashes in the **Governance Ledger**.  

> *“Transformation turns data into alignment — geometry into governance.”*

---

## 🗂️ Directory Layout
```text
data/work/tmp/hazards/transforms/
├── flood_extents_cf/                # Harmonized flood datasets (COG/GeoTIFF)
├── tornado_tracks_cf/               # Tornado tracks normalized CRS/attributes
├── wildfire_perimeters_cf/          # MODIS/VIIRS/USGS fire data harmonized
├── usdm_drought_cf/                 # Weekly drought indices aligned to CF
├── cf_fix_logs.json                 # CF compliance and attribute correction log
├── reprojection_trace.log           # CRS reprojection history
├── tiling_resample.log              # COG/PMTiles resampling and tiling trace
├── harmonization_summary.json       # Units, CRS, and variable harmonization report
├── spatial_resolution_audit.csv     # Input vs output resolution checks
├── transform_checksums.json         # SHA-256 hash registry
├── transform_manifest.json          # Source-to-output lineage manifest
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Make Targets (Transformation Ops)
```text
make hazards-transform-run         # Run CF harmonization, reprojection, and QA
make hazards-transform-verify      # Validate CRS, metadata, and checksums
make hazards-transform-checksum    # Generate/verify SHA-256 for all outputs
make hazards-transform-ledger      # Register transformations in Governance Ledger
```

